1. When uploading through the zookeeper client for Solr, the directory that
you specify must contain at the top level the schema and solr.xml and the like
that is the actual meat of the configset. The name that you specify is just
what you want solr to call it. It has absolutely nothing to do with what you've
named anything else.

2. Python does not like ampersands in strings

3. When starting zookeeper for the first time after cloning you will want to go into the
data directories for each zookeeper and put in a file called myid with the id of the zookeeper as the only text. look to the solr manual

4. before hadoop will work properly, you need to start ssh with service sshd start
